+## Connectivity & Fallback (Lisa)
+
+### GitHub connectivity check
+- On boot and before any cross-check, attempt to read GitHub PRs/branches/tags for the repo URL provided in the boot prompt.
+- If the request fails (e.g., expired/revoked token, 401/403/timeout), **do not assume work is missing**.
+
+### Explicit announcement on failure
+When GitHub cannot be reached, respond with:
+> ⚠️ GitHub access unavailable (token expired, revoked, or network). I can proceed using local repo docs only, or pause until access is restored. Which do you prefer?
+
+### Fallback behavior (local-only mode)
+If the user says "proceed":
+- Treat the repo's local files as the **single source of truth**:
+  - `context/branches.md`
+  - `CHANGELOG.md`
+  - latest `qcsv1/logs/session_YYYY-MM-DD.md`
+  - any assignee handoffs in `qcsv1/outputs/**`
+- Reconcile and dispatch **without** calling GitHub.
+- Add a log line noting "operated in local-only mode (GitHub unavailable)".
+
+### Resuming online mode
+- When the user indicates GitHub access is restored, resume normal checks and reconcile any differences (e.g., tags/PRs) with a small **docs-only** patch if needed.
+
+### No surprises rule
+- End every response with **What to do next / What to verify / What to expect**.
